# Skills & Projects Tracker

A full-stack Flask web application that allows users to track the technical skills they are learning and the projects they are building. This tool helps students and early-career professionals stay organized and reflect on their growth over time.

## Features

- Add and remove technical skills (e.g., Python, SQL, Git)
- Add and remove project entries, including project name and tech stack
- Displays tracked items in a clean interface
- Uses in-memory Python data structures (lists and dictionaries)
- Includes a `/debug` route to view internal data (for developers)

## Why This Project

This app demonstrates:
- A practical use of Python lists and dictionaries in a real-world context
- Full-stack development using Flask and HTML templating
- Ability to build tools that improve productivity and track progress
- A studentâ€™s initiative to reflect on and manage their technical growth

## Tech Stack

- Python 3
- Flask
- Jinja2 (HTML templating)


## How to Run the App

1. Clone this repository:
        git clone https://github.com/yourusername/skills-tracker.git
        cd skills-tracker

2. (Optional) Create and activate a virtual environment:
        python -m venv venv
        source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

3. Install Flask:
        pip install Flask

4. Run the Flask app:
        python app.py

5. Open your browser and go to:
        http://127.0.0.1:5000




